<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10047b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10047b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10047b"> 47(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> postillion</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le savant Bud&eacute;, ami d&apos;Erasme et contemporain de Fran&ccedil;ois I<sup>er</sup>, de Charles-Quint et de Luther, nous parle de: &ldquo;<mark>postillons</mark> allemands, qui, de son temps, couvraient (<i>sic</i>) les routes, portant sur leur habits un petit &eacute;cusson avec les armoiries et le nom de la ville &agrave; laquelle ils appartiennent.&rdquo; <font color="green">[The scholar Bud&eacute;, a friend of Erasmus and contemporary of Fran&ccedil;ois I, Charles V and Luther, speaks of &ldquo;German postillions who, when he was young, covered the roads bearing on their clothing a little escutcheon with the arms and name of the city to which they belonged.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 62</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01020n" href="c01all.htm#c01020n">VI.C.01:020(n)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
